The '78 Mercedes I drive has the bolt setup also. It has had no problems
in ~500,000 Miles of operation (It hasn't had a days rest since it was
purchased) with loose wheels. 
It actually has the opposite problem, when you get them on there with
the correct torque 
they are a pain to get back off. You would be in quite a situation if
you were on the side 
of the road without a long pipe to put on the wrench.

Jonathan

